<paragraph blockId="9.[264,1324,1178,1364]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
REMARKS. This is one of only two species for which males are known. 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis" box="[1129,1323,1178,1204]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. (1993) Catalog of the types of southern African Mythicomyiidae (Insecta: Diptera). Genus, 4, 91 - 102." type="journal article" year="1993">
Evenhuis (
<number box="[1253,1314,1178,1204]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
examined the 
<typeStatus box="[434,484,1218,1244]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">type</typeStatus>
material in 
<collectionCode box="[635,723,1218,1244]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">BMNH</collectionCode>
and designated the male as 
<typeStatus box="[1070,1181,1218,1244]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">lectotype</typeStatus>
. No further material has since been found of this species in collections consulted. The original description and salient characters given in 
<bibRefCitation author="Hesse" box="[688,846,1298,1324]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" refString="Hesse, A. J. (1938) Revision of the Bombyliidae of Southern Africa. Annals of the South African Museum, 34, 1 - 1053." type="journal article" year="1938">
Hesse (
<number box="[776,837,1298,1324]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" value="1938.0">1938</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
serve to adequately distinguish the species.
</paragraph>
